1 Department of Kentucky State Police and who shall report to the
2 executive director of the Office of Technical Services; and
3 c. Division of Records Management, which shall be headed by a
4 director who shall be appointed by the commissioner of the
5 Department of Kentucky State Police and who shall report to the
6 executive director of the Office of Technical Services; and
7 (e) Department of Public Advocacy, which shall have the following divisions:
8 1. Protection and Advocacy Division;
9 2. Division of Law Operations;
10 3. Division of Trial Services;
11 4. Division of Post-Trial Services;
12 5. Division of Conflict and Contract Services; and
13 6. Division of Education, Strategic Planning, and Recruitment.
14 (2) Each department, except for the Department of Public Advocacy, shall be headed
15 by a commissioner who shall be appointed by the secretary of the Justice and Public
16 Safety Cabinet with the approval of the Governor as required by KRS 12.040. Each
17 commissioner shall be directly responsible to the secretary and shall have[ such]
18 functions, powers, and duties as provided by law and as the secretary may
19 prescribe. The Department of Public Advocacy shall be headed by the public
20 advocate, appointed as required by KRS 31.020, who shall be directly responsible
21 to the Public Advocacy Commission. The Department of Public Advocacy is an
22 independent state agency which shall be attached to the Justice and Public Safety
23 Cabinet for administrative purposes only. The Justice and Public Safety Cabinet
24 shall not have control over the Department of Public Advocacy's information
25 technology equipment and use unless granted access by court order.
26 (3) The Justice and Public Safety Cabinet shall have the following offices and
27 divisions:
