1 (a) Office of the Secretary, which shall be headed by a deputy secretary
2 appointed pursuant to KRS 12.050 and responsible for the direct
3 administrative support for the secretary and other duties as assigned by the
4 secretary, and which, with the approval of the secretary, may employ[ such]
5 staff as necessary to perform the duties, functions, and responsibilities of the
6 office;
7 (b) Office of Human Resource Management, which shall be headed by an
8 executive director appointed pursuant to KRS 12.050 who shall be responsible
9 to and report to the secretary and be responsible for all matters relating to
10 human resources, and who, with the approval of the secretary, may employ[
11 such] staff as necessary to perform the duties, functions, and responsibilities
12 of the office;
13 1. Division of Human Resource Administration, which shall be headed by
14 a director appointed pursuant to KRS 12.050 who shall report to the
15 executive director of the Office of Human Resource Management; and
16 2. Division of Employee Management, which shall be headed by a director
17 appointed pursuant to KRS 12.050 who shall report to the executive
18 director of the Office of Human Resource Management;
19 (c) Office of Legal Services, which shall be headed by an executive director
20 appointed pursuant to KRS 12.050 and 12.210, that:
21 1. Shall provide legal representation and services for the cabinet; and
22 2. May investigate all complaints regarding the facilities, staff, treatment
23 of juveniles, and other matters relating to the operation of the Justice
24 and Public Safety Cabinet. If it appears that there is a violation of
25 statutes, administrative regulations, policies, court decisions, the rights
26 of juveniles who are subject to the orders of the department, or any other
27 matter relating to the Justice and Public Safety Cabinet, the office shall
