14 (i) Office of Drug Control Policy, which shall be headed by an executive director
15 appointed pursuant to KRS 12.050 who shall be responsible for all matters
16 relating to the research, coordination, and execution of drug control policy
17 and for the management of state and federal grants, including but not limited
18 to the prevention and treatment related to substance abuse. By December 31
19 of each year, the Office of Drug Control Policy shall review, approve, and
20 coordinate all current projects of any substance abuse program which is
21 conducted by or receives funding through agencies of the executive branch.
22 This oversight shall extend to all substance abuse programs which are
23 principally related to the prevention or treatment, or otherwise targeted at the
24 reduction, of substance abuse in the Commonwealth. The Office of Drug
25 Control Policy shall promulgate administrative regulations consistent with
26 enforcing this oversight authority. The executive director shall be directly
27 responsible to and report to the secretary and may employ[ such] staff as
